cu500_pal | 1 | The author wrote careless and inconsistent notes in the margins of the four pages and in other blank spaces.  He seems to have been conscious of the central division of the sheet into pages, although in one instance he began his formula on the inner margin of page 4 and finished it on the adjoining inner margin of page 1.  The script is typical of the function and period, but not as neatly executed as in some actual legal documents.  It is extremely cursive and complicated with unorthodox ligatures, joining letters that should not be joined and running several words together.  Careless abbreviations and lack of diacritical points abound.  It is impossible to determine the order in which the author made his entries.
