cu590_con | 1 | Two joined folios of light brown paper of fine texture, partly discolored and considerably damaged with much of the lower half of both folios lost.  There are six distinct entries written in different scripts and with overlapping inks.  By the time the legal testimonies were written, the two folios had been separated from the rest of the volume and were no longer folios, but were flat sheets of scrap paper.
